  "prompt": "What do you put in a resignation letter?",
  "response": "A resignation letter typically includes:\n\n1. Date of writing\n\n2. Your current position and department\n\n3. Your intended last working day (usually two weeks from the date of the letter)\n\n4. A brief, professional statement of resignation\n\n5. A thank you for the opportunities provided\n\n6. An offer to help with the transition\n\n7. Your signature\n\nExample template:\n[Your Name]\n[Your Address]\n[Date]\n\n[Manager's Name]\n[Company Name]\n\nDear [Manager's Name],\n\nI am writing to formally resign from my position as [job title] at [company name], effective [date - typically two weeks from the letter date].\n\nI appreciate the opportunities for professional and personal development that you have provided me during my time at [company name].\n\nI am committed to ensuring a smooth transition and will do my best to complete any outstanding projects before my departure.\n\nSincerely,\n[Your Signature]\n[Your Printed Name]\n\nKey tips:\n- Keep it professional and positive\n- Be concise\n- Avoid negative comments\n- Maintain a grateful tone\n- Proofread before submitting",
